# 🏦 FinTrack Bank — Banking Analytics Pipeline

> A simulated consulting engagement built for DataBridge Consulting — an end-to-end banking analytics pipeline that identifies financially at-risk customers using Python, SQL, and data engineering best practices.

---

## 📋 Project Background

FinTrack Bank is a mid-sized retail bank concerned about rising customer default rates. As the Junior Business Analyst on this engagement, I was tasked with building a data pipeline, analysing customer financial behaviour, and delivering actionable insights to senior management.

---

## 🏗️ Architecture

```
REST API + Generated Data
        ↓
    Extract()
        ↓
    Validate()  ← Pydantic schema enforcement
        ↓
   Transform()  ← pandas cleaning & reshaping
        ↓
     Load()     ← SQLite database (fintrack.db)
        ↓
  SQL Analysis  ← 6 business questions
        ↓
 Visualizations ← matplotlib charts
        ↓
Executive Summary
```

---

## 📡 Data Sources

| Source | Type | Records | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| JSONPlaceholder `/users` | REST API | 10 | Customer profiles |
| Generated Transactions | Python | 500 | 6 months of banking transactions |

---

## 🗄️ Database Schema

```
fintrack.db
  ├── users         (id, name, username, email, phone, website)
  └── transactions  (id, userId, amount, type, category, date, balance_after)
```

**Relationship:** `transactions.userId` → `users.id` (Many-to-One)

---

## ❓ Business Questions Answered

| # | Question | SQL Technique |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Average balance by transaction type | GROUP BY + AVG |
| 2 | Customers below $500 danger threshold | JOIN + WHERE |
| 3 | Transaction volume and value by type | GROUP BY + COUNT + SUM |
| 4 | Most active customers | JOIN + COUNT + ORDER BY |
| 5 | Monthly transaction trend | strftime + GROUP BY |
| 6 | Risk flag — customers who spent more than earned | CTE + CASE WHEN + JOIN |

